tornado/wsgi.py
==================
c87e84f;Ben Darnell;2010-04-21 13:57:05 -0700;cStringIO's constructor uses a 16-bit encoding when given a unicode string.  This is inconsistent with its write method, which encodes all strings as ascii (and rejects unicode strings iff they have any non-ascii characters).  This change uses utf-8 as the default encoding when constructing cStringIO objects in tornado.

